            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science invested over $1.8 million in CO-01 institutions and businesses between FY2023 and FY2025\n* Urban Sky Theory Inc in Denver ($1.2M grant) is developing real-time wildfire detection and communication systems\n* University of Denver researchers are funded by NASA to study the lifecycle of stars and cosmic dust\n* Sustains local high-tech employment at Denver-based contractors including Drivendata, Inc. ($419,200) and Trace3 Government, LLC",
            "rationale": "Cites specific spending data for CO-01, including the $1.8M total and specific grants to Urban Sky Theory Inc and University of Denver, plus contract data for Drivendata and Trace3.",
